  Dialogue:
  - The following week <color=yellow>Captain Parovy</color> was furious.
  - "<color=purple>William</color>, you\u2026."
  - He took a deep breath and lowered his voice.
  - Is it true that you refused a bribe from a betting house and arrested the attendant?
  - Yes.
  - Why the hell didn't you take the fucking bribe?
  - Because that would be against the <color=yellow>law</color>.
  - <color=yellow>Parovy</color> was having trouble controlling himself.
  - <color=purple>William</color>, is your salary good?
  - Ye...
  - No! It is not. The salary of all warriors sucks because we risked our damn lives
    and there's no money to pay for it.
  - The betting houses are our extra income and there's no reason to refuse the damn
    bribes. Nobody gains anything from it.
  - <color=yellow>Capta</color>...
  - Nobody! What were you thinking? Gambling is a minor misdemeanor, the guy would
    be in jail for a maximum of 20 days, why the hell would we fight with the betting
    houses?
  - "<color=yellow>Captain</color>! It is not our duty to legislate, we just follow
    the\u2026"
  - Silence! You've given me a huge amount of work these days, luckily I managed
    to negotiate with the betting houses, they'll ignore the shit you did as long
    as I release the guy you arrested and fire you.
  - <color=purple>William</color> wasn't going to beg for forgiveness, he just looked
    at him with contempt in his eyes, hoping that would upset <color=yellow>Captain
    Parovy</color>.
  - It may not seem like it, <color=purple>William</color>, but this is for your
    own good, otherwise the betting houses would hire an assassin to kill you.
  DialogueBR:
  - "Na semana seguinte, o <color=yellow>Capit\xE3o Parovy</color> ficou furioso."
  - "<color=purple>William</color>, voc\xEA\u2026."
  - Ele respirou fundo e baixou a voz.
  - "\xC9 verdade que voc\xEA recusou um suborno de uma casa de apostas e prendeu
    o atendente?"
  - Sim.
  - "Por que diabos voc\xEA n\xE3o aceitou a porra do suborno?"
  - Porque isso seria contra a <color=yellow>lei</color>.
  - <color=yellow>Parovy</color> estava tendo problemas para se controlar.
  - "<color=purple>William</color>, seu sal\xE1rio \xE9 bom?"
  - Si...
  - "N\xE3o! N\xE3o \xE9. O sal\xE1rio de todos os guerreiros \xE9 uma merda porque
    arriscamos nossas vidas e n\xE3o h\xE1 dinheiro para pagar por isso."
  - "As casas de apostas s\xE3o nossa renda extra e n\xE3o h\xE1 raz\xE3o para recusar
    os malditos subornos. Ningu\xE9m ganha nada com isso."
  - "<color=yellow>Capit\xE3</color>..."
  - "Ningu\xE9m! O que voc\xEA estava pensando? Jogo de azar \xE9 uma contraven\xE7\xE3o
    leve, o cara ficaria preso no m\xE1ximo 20 dias, por que diabos n\xF3s ir\xEDamos
    brigar com as casas de apostas?"
  - "<color=yellow>Capit\xE3o</color>! N\xE3o \xE9 nosso dever legislar, n\xF3s apenas
    seguimos a\u2026"
  - "Sil\xEAncio! Voc\xEA me deu muito trabalho esses dias, felizmente consegui negociar
    com as casas de apostas, eles v\xE3o ignorar a merda que voc\xEA fez desde que
    eu solte o cara que voc\xEA prendeu e demito voc\xEA."
  - "<color=purple>William</color> n\xE3o ia implorar por perd\xE3o, ele apenas o
    olhou com desprezo nos olhos, esperando que isso incomodasse o <color=yellow>Capit\xE3o
    Parovy</color>."
  - "Pode n\xE3o parecer, <color=purple>William</color>, mas isso \xE9 para seu pr\xF3prio
    bem, caso contr\xE1rio as casas de apostas contratariam um assassino para assassin\xE1-lo."
